<ns2952:section xmlns:ns2952="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.mda.introduction.whyUseMda">

  <ns2953:title xmlns:ns2953="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Why use the MDA</ns2953:title>
  <ns2954:para xmlns:ns2954="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    There are a number of advantages of formally using MDA:
    <ns2955:itemizedlist xmlns:ns2955="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns2956:listitem xmlns:ns2956="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2957:formalpara xmlns:ns2957="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns2958:title xmlns:ns2958="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Architectures are longer-lived</ns2958:title>
        <ns2959:para xmlns:ns2959="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          Since the architecture is decoupled from any implementation technology,
          it is able to survive technology changes.
        </ns2959:para>
      </ns2957:formalpara></ns2956:listitem>
      <ns2960:listitem xmlns:ns2960="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2961:formalpara xmlns:ns2961="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns2962:title xmlns:ns2962="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Derive code from a stable model</ns2962:title>
        <ns2963:para xmlns:ns2963="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          The MDA enables one to derive and potentially automatically generate code from
          a platform-independent model which <ns2964:emphasis xmlns:ns2964="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">remains stable as the underlying
          infrastructure evolves over time</ns2964:emphasis> onto various evolving infrastructure
          technologies.
        </ns2963:para>
      </ns2961:formalpara></ns2960:listitem>
      <ns2965:listitem xmlns:ns2965="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2966:formalpara xmlns:ns2966="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns2967:title xmlns:ns2967="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Cost-effective porting to other platforms/technologies</ns2967:title>
        <ns2968:para xmlns:ns2968="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          Since MDA specifies a mapping process from the PIM to the PSM, a change
          in platform simply requires a change in the mapping layer. <ns2969:emphasis xmlns:ns2969="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">If 
          standard mappings are used the system becomes fully portable.</ns2969:emphasis> 
          The PSM is then generated from the PIM (which remains unchanged) through the new, 
          technology-specific mapping.
        </ns2968:para>
      </ns2966:formalpara></ns2965:listitem>
      <ns2970:listitem xmlns:ns2970="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2971:formalpara xmlns:ns2971="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns2972:title xmlns:ns2972="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Increased productivity</ns2972:title>
        <ns2973:para xmlns:ns2973="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          Only the PIM needs to be maintained. New PSMs within changing technologies and the
          resultant code can be auto-generated. This leads to improved productivity and hence
          to <ns2974:emphasis xmlns:ns2974="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">lower cost</ns2974:emphasis> and <ns2975:emphasis xmlns:ns2975="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">reduced time-to-market</ns2975:emphasis>.
          <ns2976:note xmlns:ns2976="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2977:para xmlns:ns2977="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            In an article, <ns2978:quote xmlns:ns2978="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2979:emphasis xmlns:ns2979="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Driving business agility with model driven
            architecture</ns2979:emphasis></ns2978:quote>, eds.com claims that using 
            MDA within <ns2980:emphasis xmlns:ns2980="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">OptimalJ</ns2980:emphasis> they reduced the number of lines of
            code for the Java PetStore example by more than a factor 10.
          </ns2977:para></ns2976:note>  
        </ns2973:para>
      </ns2971:formalpara></ns2970:listitem>
      <ns2981:listitem xmlns:ns2981="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2982:formalpara xmlns:ns2982="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns2983:title xmlns:ns2983="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">It is easier to evaluate the choice of implementation technology</ns2983:title>
        <ns2984:para xmlns:ns2984="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          The difference between the mappings encapsulates the difference in technology
          choices.
        </ns2984:para>
      </ns2982:formalpara></ns2981:listitem>
      <ns2985:listitem xmlns:ns2985="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2986:formalpara xmlns:ns2986="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns2987:title xmlns:ns2987="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Improved quality</ns2987:title>
        <ns2988:para xmlns:ns2988="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          The quality of the PSM is largely determined by the quality of mapping and not on the
          understanding the individual developers have of the PIM and of the implementation
          technologies. These standard mappings can be expected to perform solid technology
          mappings.
        </ns2988:para>
      </ns2986:formalpara></ns2985:listitem>
      <ns2989:listitem xmlns:ns2989="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2990:formalpara xmlns:ns2990="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns2991:title xmlns:ns2991="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Rapid inclusion of emerging technology benefits</ns2991:title>
        <ns2992:para xmlns:ns2992="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        
        </ns2992:para>
      </ns2990:formalpara></ns2989:listitem>
    </ns2955:itemizedlist>
  </ns2954:para>
</ns2952:section>